## ccrotate — Auto-rotate on rate limit

When you see ANY of these messages in the conversation:
- "You've hit your session limit"
- "You've hit your weekly limit"
- "You're now using extra usage"
- "You're out of extra usage"

Do this IMMEDIATELY without waiting for user input:
1. Run `ccrotate refresh` to get current usage tiers + reset times
2. Read `ccrotate tier-cache` for reset epochs
3. If any account shows "base" tier → run `ccrotate next` to switch, then continue work
4. If ALL accounts are extra/exhausted → parse the earliest `rateLimits.reset5h` or `reset7d` epoch from the cache, convert to local cron time (2 min after reset), and schedule a one-shot `CronCreate` with prompt: "Rate limit reset. Run ccrotate refresh, show results. If base tier available, run ccrotate next to switch. Then continue previous work."
5. Tell the user what happened and when base usage will be available
<!-- CCROTATE:END -->
